  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Compliance Officer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Department/Location</strong></u></p><p>Investment Management / Singapore Office</p><p></p><p><u><strong>Compliance Function</strong></u></p><p>- Reporting directly to the Board of Directors</p><ul><li>Monitors the company’s compliance accordance to regulatory guidelines and company policies</li><li>Performing AML/ CFT and CDD related tasks on the new investors independently and coordinating the results with Fund Administrators, including KYC checks and AML/CFT related tasks, </li><li>CDD screenings using various available platforms and databases</li><li>Ensure proper completions of the subscription documents and ensuring KYC requirements are certified and in good order</li><li>Tracking regulatory developments. Accordingly involved in the review and update the various frameworks, processes and procedures</li><li>Liaisons with various external parties including corporate and HNI, overseas state government offices, solicitors, financial institutions, etc</li><li>Adhere to compliance with financial services legislation, industry and professional codes of practice</li><li>Prepare and administer compliance training for new employees and continuous training for team members</li><li>Involved in the recruitment of new employees and termination. Induction training for new joiners and ensuring the proper handover of role before resignation/ termination.</li><li>Providing compliance advice and guidance on related issues to senior managers</li><li>Prepare reports and presentations to Board of Directors</li><li>Facilitate external and internal audit</li></ul><p><u><strong>Necessary Knowledge and Skills</strong></u></p><ul><li>Education: Degree (preferably a business/finance degree)</li><li>Minimum 6 years of working experience ( candidates experienced in financial /asset management industry will be preferred)</li><li>Good interpersonal skills</li></ul><p><u><strong>Other requirements</strong></u></p><p>Singapore Citizen / PR (please state in the resume)</p>",
